						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in front of the Hanumān temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 12th Century.</p>						

						<p>This commences with the <hi rend="italic">pras11asti</hi> of a Chālukya king whose name is lost, and seems to register a gift. In the later part are mentioned Maṇi Nāgōja and a gift to a carpenter. The epigraph is much damaged.</p>						

